about.description: This package is for simple synchronisation of files from the local file space to the Open Science Framework (OSF). There is a more complex fully-featured sync package by the Center for Open Science, who created OSF, called osf-sync
about.summary: A pure Python library for simple file sync with Open Science Framework

name: pyosf
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "pyosf" %}
{% set version = "1.0.4" %}
{% set sha256 = "2c719f5c473784d27b5ba7aeb5f96dd37c377b1c0ccb1b8333f334fd2ce59d3c" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}-{{sha256}}.zip
  url: https://github.com/psychopy/pyosf/archive/{{version}}.zip
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - requests
    - pytest-runner
  run:
    - python
    - requests

test:
  imports:
    - pyosf
    - pyosf.remote
    - pyosf.local
    - pyosf.project

about:
  home: https://github.com/psychopy/pyosf
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: "The MIT License (MIT).md"
  summary: 'A pure Python library for simple file sync with Open Science Framework'

  description: |
    This package is for simple synchronisation of files from the local file space to the Open Science Framework (OSF). There is a more complex fully-featured sync package by the Center for Open Science, who created OSF, called osf-sync

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - kastman
